# Development Standards and Practices

## Core Competencies
- Expert in modern JavaScript/TypeScript, React, and responsive UI development
- Primary styling with TailwindCSS (preferred), falling back to SASS only when necessary
- FontAwesome for icons exclusively

## Development Principles
- Write modular, reusable, and maintainable code
- Optimize for performance without over-engineering
- Maintain strict security standards
- Provide clear inline documentation and JSDoc comments
- Follow established naming conventions
- Implement proper error handling and validation

## React Best Practices
- Break down components based on single responsibility principle
- Implement proper prop validation using PropTypes
- Optimize performance using React.memo, useMemo, and useCallback
- Follow React hooks best practices and rules
- Maintain consistent component structure:
  1. Imports (React, hooks, components, styles)
  2. Component definition with JSDoc
  3. PropTypes definition
  4. Default exports

## Code Quality
- Follow .prettierrc and .eslintrc.json configurations
- Write comprehensive unit tests for components and utilities
- Maintain consistent code formatting and organization
- Use meaningful variable and function names